"title": "7217: exile, in Babylon",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7217: exile, in babylon",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The southern kingdom of Judah was conquered by Babylon under Nebuchadnezzar. Before and after the destruction of Jerusalem in 587 B.C. the population was taken into exile in three stages.</p>\n<h2>The entire episode was within the purposes of God and under his control</h2>\n<h3>The reason for the captivity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:11-2Kgs21:15\">2KI 21:11–21:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:1\">1CH 9:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:7\">EZR 9:7</a></p>\n<h3>The captivity foretold by the prophets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa39:5-Isa39:7\">ISA 39:5–39:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:14-Jer1:16\">JER 1:14–1:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:17\">JER 13:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:19\">JER 13:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek12:11\">EZK 12:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek21:24\">EZK 21:24</a></p>\n<h3>Babylon the instrument of God's chastisement of Judah</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:25\">JER 22:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:8-Jer25:11\">JER 25:8–25:11</a></p>\n<h3>A remnant would be spared</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek12:16\">EZK 12:16</a></p>\n<h2>The historical details</h2>\n<h3>Nebuchadnezzar marches against Jerusalem</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:1-Dan1:2\">DAN 1:1–1:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:1-2Kgs25:21\">2KI 25:1–25:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:17-2Chr36:20\">2CH 36:17–36:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer39:1-Jer39:10\">JER 39:1–39:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:4-Jer52:27\">JER 52:4–52:27</a></p>\n<h3>The people of Judah are taken into exile in three stages</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer52:27-Jer52:30\">JER 52:27–52:30</a></strong></p>\n<h2>God watches over his people during their captivity</h2>\n<h3>The LORD hears and answers the prayers of his people in captivity</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:33\">PSA 69:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:17-Dan9:23\">DAN 9:17–9:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:12-Dan10:14\">DAN 10:12–10:14</a></p>\n<h3>Babylon spares certain captives, and gives them some freedom and dignity</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:27-2Kgs25:30\">2KI 25:27–25:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan1:12-Dan1:20\">DAN 1:12–1:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:48-Dan2:49\">DAN 2:48–2:49</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:30\">DAN 3:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:28\">DAN 6:28</a></p>\n<h3>God encourages his people during their captivity</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:33\">PSA 69:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer29:11\">JER 29:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:37-Ezek36:38\">EZK 36:37–36:38</a></p>\n<h2>Promises of eventual restoration</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:8\">EZK 36:8</a></p>\n<h3>The promise of return from exile</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer33:7-Jer33:8\">JER 33:7–33:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer16:15\">JER 16:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:3\">JER 23:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer24:5-Jer24:7\">JER 24:5–24:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer27:22\">JER 27:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer29:14\">JER 29:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:3\">JER 30:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:27-Jer31:28\">JER 31:27–31:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam4:22\">LAM 4:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:12-Ezek34:13\">EZK 34:12–34:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:20\">ZEP 3:20</a></p>\n<h3>Restoration to be a demonstration of God's grace</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:22\">EZK 36:22</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The promise of covenant renewal</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:31-Jer31:34\">JER 31:31–31:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:25\">EZK 34:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:26-Ezek36:27\">EZK 36:26–36:27</a></p>\n<h3>The promise of return fulfilled</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:22-2Chr36:23\">2CH 36:22–36:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra1:1-Ezra1:3\">EZR 1:1–1:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh7:6\">NEH 7:6</a></p>\n<h2>Babylonian oppressors to be punished</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:12-Jer25:14\">JER 25:12–25:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:16\">JER 30:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:18\">JER 50:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:49\">JER 51:49</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:55-Jer51:56\">JER 51:55–51:56</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:64\">JER 51:64</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:7\">EZK 36:7</a></p>",
